media:group.media:title: Is Finnish Language Hard To Learn:cases that determine LOCATION
media:group.media:description:
Is Finnish Language Hard To Learn: cases that determine LOCATION.
As we know in Finnish there are no prepositions like “In”, “from” or “to”.  So instead, we add endings to the words. And in the case of location, we need to distinguish, whether the location is in a closed space or open space.
